Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1%unit}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the tomatoes to the #bowl{} of dressing and set aside for later.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the
stalks).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}, @honey{15%grams},
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams} and half the chopped mint.
> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for
  ~{1%minute} to loosen.
> TIP: Use less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Season with salt and pepper, then set your 'Nduja yoghurt aside.

When the chips have about ~{10%minutes} remaining, place the
@ready to eat falafels{171%grams} onto a lined baking tray and bake on the
middle shelf until golden brown, ~{5-8%minutes}.

A couple mins before the falafels are ready, pop your @plain taco tortillas{4}
into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Just before everything's ready, toss the baby gem with the tomatoes and
dressing.

To make your wraps, lay the tortillas on your plates.

Top with the falafels and some of the salad. Drizzle over the 'Nduja yoghurt
and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams}. Sprinkle the remaining
mint over to finish and fold in the sides of the tortillas to make your wraps.

Serve with the chips and any remaining salad on the side.

Enjoy!